      "unit": "역삼각함수",
      "concept": "tan⁻¹x + tan⁻¹(1/x) = π/2",
      "difficulty": "easy",
      "question": "$a_n=\\tan^{-1}n$, $b_n=\\tan^{-1}\\dfrac{1}{n}$일 때, 다음 중 모든 자연수 $n$에 대하여 옳은 것은?",
      "options": [
        {"id":"1","label":"1","text":"$a_n+b_n=\\dfrac{\\pi}{2}$","contentType":"latex","image":""},
        {"id":"2","label":"2","text":"$a_n-b_n=\\dfrac{\\pi}{4}$","contentType":"latex","image":""},
        {"id":"3","label":"3","text":"$a_n b_n=1$","contentType":"latex","image":""},
        {"id":"4","label":"4","text":"$a_n b_n=\\dfrac{\\pi}{4}$","contentType":"latex","image":""}
      ],
      "correct_option_id": "1",
      "explanation": "공식 $\\tan^{-1}x+\\tan^{-1}\\dfrac{1}{x}=\\dfrac{\\pi}{2}$ ($x>0$).\n따라서 $a_n+b_n=\\dfrac{\\pi}{2}$.",
      "tags": ["daily","미분학","역삼각함수"]
    },
    {
      "id": "q-daily-r1-2",
      "subject": "미분학",
      "unit": "역삼각함수",
